<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 93-05-01 - Correct Rattle in Douglas Single Lever Model 929 Steering Column</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi930501" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>93-05-01</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>June, 1993</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>STEERING</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Correct Rattle in Douglas Single Lever Model 929 Steering Column</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Douglas</vendor>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9400</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI describes how to correct a rattle in the Douglas Single Lever Model 929 Steering Column
                    on 9200, 9300 and 9400 truck models.
                </para>
                <para>If a complaint of a rattling sound is received and the vehicle has a Douglas single lever Model
                    929 steering column, the rattling sound may be due to clearance between the steering column lower
                    shaft outside diameter and the steering column lower bearing inside diameter. Effective with May
                    production, a tolerance ring has been installed on the lower shaft to correct this condition.
                </para>
                <para>To determine if the rattle is coming from the steering column, locate the universal joint on the
                    intermediate shaft that attaches to the lower shaft of the steering column. Grasp the intermediate
                    shaft at the universal joint yoke. Push and pull toward the right and left side of the vehicle,
                    checking for looseness between the lower steering column shaft and lower bearing. If the lower
                    steering column shaft appears to be moving in the bearing, perform the following procedure.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
