        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9305011">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                for the following steps.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9305011" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9305011.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Lower Steering Column Shaft and Intermediate Shaft Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PINCH BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SNAP RING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOWER SHAFT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. PLASTIC CONE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. INTERMEDIATE SHAFT YOKE</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. INTERMEDIATE SHAFT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pinch bolt from the U-joint yoke.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the intermediate shaft off the lower column shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard the snap ring that is against the lower bearing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the plastic cone from the anti-rattle kit over the end of the shaft with the
                    tapered end toward the bearing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the spring from the anti-rattle kit over the shaft until is seated against the
                    flat side of the plastic cone.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the intermediate shaft so it is applying pressure against the bearing through
                    the spring and plastic cone.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the pinch bolt; tighten to 70-75 ft-lbs. (95-105 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the steering wheel FULL RIGHT and FULL LEFT against the stops to insure that there
                    are no catches, binding or other irregularities due to the installation of the anti-rattle kit.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
